"""Seeded randomness — every value derives from one `random.Random(seed)` so a
given (--tier, --seed) reproduces byte-for-byte. No third-party deps (no Faker):
stdlib random + curated pools (pools.py) give tighter control over the referential
consistency §2 demands than Faker would.
